The paper deals with weakly supervised instance labeling using multiple instance learning (MIL) and proposes a novel regularization strategy based on virtual adversarial training for improving MIL training. The paper also introduces a knowledge distillation technique for repurposing the trained MIL model. Given that the paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with regularization and knowledge distillation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with artificial intelligence techniques for medical image analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with natural language processing techniques for medical image analysis, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
